               <p>JONATHAN ORME. I am a <rs id="t18280221-168-viclabel893" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-168-victim1023 t18280221-168-viclabel893"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-168-crimeloc894">Little<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210105"></xptr>Russel-street, Covent-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-168-crimeloc894" type="placeName" value="Little182802210105Russel-street, Covent-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-168-crimeloc894" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-168-off891 t18280221-168-crimeloc894"></join>. On the 12th of February, about half-past four o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came in for the purpose of begging charity; I had given him a waistcoat, a pair of trousers, a hat, and a shilling, three weeks before; I was engaged in serving a customer; he walked down the shop, and stood before the fire; while I was at the top of the shop I saw him walk up hastily, and he said he would call again as I was busy; I said I would attend to him directly, and asked what he wanted; he began to tell me a long tale of his distresses, and I saw under his lame arm a parcel, which I knew was my own; I took hold of him, and asked what it was; he said it was some thread and needles which he mended his clothes with - he did not wish me to see it, but I took hold of it, and it was my own.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-168-person1024">
                  JOHN 
                  ALDERSON
               <interp inst="t18280221-168-person1024" type="surname" value="ALDERSON"></interp>
